Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

I checked the relationship between the employment status and borrower rate to see how the employment status affect the loan rate.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

I observed that the higher the income range, the lower the APR. The relationship between the loan status and borrower APR showed that borrowers with low APR have completed their loan payment. Further analysis into the employment status would give more insights.

Conclusions¶

The APR of borrowers with $0 need to be reviewed to prevent long term payment of the loan or inability to repay the loan.

While checking the relationship between the borrower rate and employment status, i decided to add the 'IsBorrowerHomeowner' to know if the borrower owns a home. I observed that most of the home owners are unemployed. This most likely mean that they used their homes as collateral. Most would likely lose their home due to inability to repay the loan before the stipulated time.

The observations shows the correlation between the features of the dataset and how they affect the loan outcome, the laon term and even the inetrest rate. Further exploration into the dataset would give a more indepth result.
